HEADWORD: Optimate
<hw>Op"ti*mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>optimas</ets>, <ets>-atis</ets>, adj., <ets>optimates</ets>, n.
pl., the adherents of the best men, the aristocrats, fr.
<ets>optimus</ets> the best.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the
nobility or aristocracy.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>A nobleman or aristocrat; a chief man in a state or
city.</def></def2> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

